Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.71,0:11:32.88,Episode Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an5\pos(636,349.733)\fad(250,0)\b1\c&H030004&\fscx151\fscy156}Hyouka
Dialogue: 9,0:11:41.97,0:11:43.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Morning already?
Dialogue: 9,0:11:46.73,0:11:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, morning!
Dialogue: 9,0:11:48.14,0:11:48.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Morning.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:48.93,0:11:50.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are the others?
Dialogue: 9,0:11:51.64,0:11:53.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw it.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:53.44,0:11:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Saw what, now?
Dialogue: 9,0:11:55.27,0:11:59.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Last night, I woke up in the middle of the night...
Dialogue: 9,0:11:59.06,0:12:05.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And when I turned over, in the room across from ours, I saw a hanged shadow swaying back and forth!
Dialogue: 9,0:12:05.68,0:12:08.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's pretty rare to see Ibara panicking like this.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:08.05,0:12:11.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Too bad you're not here to see it, Satoshi.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:11.00,0:12:12.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for the meal.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:12.73,0:12:14.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How was the bath?
Dialogue: 9,0:12:14.42,0:12:16.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was absolutely wonderful!
Dialogue: 9,0:12:16.18,0:12:17.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's good!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.50,0:12:17.04,Handwriting,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fay-0.5\fs50\fnBurst My Bubble\b0\c&H1E2A2F&\pos(719.682,388.349)}Rie{\b1}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.04,0:12:18.34,Handwriting,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fay-0.1\blur1\fs150\fnBurst My Bubble\b1\c&H222525&\pos(564.025,355.892)}Rie{\b0}
Dialogue: 9,0:12:18.34,0:12:20.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And wasn't your futon nice and soft?
Dialogue: 9,0:12:20.63,0:12:23.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! I slept wonderfully!
Dialogue: 9,0:12:23.05,0:12:24.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like Kayo didn't write hers.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:25.89,0:12:29.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't know you were scared of stories like that, Maya-neechan.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:29.89,0:12:32.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like I'm scared of ghosts!
Dialogue: 9,0:12:32.61,0:12:34.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But when you see something like that...
Dialogue: 9,0:12:34.90,0:12:36.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just disturbing!
Dialogue: 9,0:12:37.65,0:12:39.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maya-neechan... You saw it?
Dialogue: 9,0:12:39.40,0:12:40.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw it. I definitely saw it. I really saw it!
Dialogue: 9,0:12:40.98,0:12:43.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Onee-chan! You told them that story?
Dialogue: 9,0:12:43.45,0:12:45.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad said not to tell anyone!
Dialogue: 9,0:12:45.68,0:12:49.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on. It's just Maya-neechan.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:53.46,0:12:54.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 9,0:12:55.56,0:13:00.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think of Mayaka-san's story?
Dialogue: 9,0:13:00.06,0:13:01.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The hanged shadow?
Dialogue: 9,0:13:02.78,0:13:07.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure it's one of those things that every inn probably has.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:07.72,0:13:11.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, do you think what Mayaka-san says is true?
Dialogue: 9,0:13:11.77,0:13:13.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:13.94,0:13:16.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then perhaps I'm mistaken as well.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:17.12,0:13:18.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 9,0:13:21.07,0:13:24.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw it too. A hanged shadow.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:24.57,0:13:27.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Mayaka-san woke up, I did too.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:28.25,0:13:30.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I saw it swaying in the dark.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:31.39,0:13:36.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I was mistaken, but Mayaka-san said she saw the same thing...
Dialogue: 9,0:13:36.42,0:13:38.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You probably just mistook something else for it.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:38.76,0:13:41.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like Satoshi was saying yesterday, "The ghost, when examined..."
Dialogue: 9,0:13:41.63,0:13:43.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"...was just withered flowers"?
Dialogue: 9,0:13:45.26,0:13:46.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 9,0:13:46.76,0:13:48.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What exactly did I see?
Dialogue: 9,0:13:48.99,0:13:50.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:50.35,0:13:53.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell us what it was we saw, then.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:53.10,0:13:54.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do I—
Dialogue: 9,0:13:54.12,0:13:56.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's look into it!
Dialogue: 9,0:13:56.48,0:13:58.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm curious!
Dialogue: 9,0:14:00.37,0:14:01.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Chii-chan!
Dialogue: 9,0:14:01.23,0:14:04.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told Rie that I would help her with her homework!
Dialogue: 9,0:14:04.61,0:14:06.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave it to us!
Dialogue: 9,0:14:06.24,0:14:08.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll discover the truth behind this mystery!
Dialogue: 9,0:14:08.64,0:14:10.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Oreki-san?
Dialogue: 9,0:14:10.12,0:14:11.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ask me.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:11.78,0:14:16.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, if I have to do it, make it quick.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:12.17,0:14:13.05,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,{overlap}Excuse us.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:16.12,0:14:20.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, so you saw this hanged shadow in the room across from yours?
Dialogue: 9,0:14:20.33,0:14:22.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:22.16,0:14:23.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How big was it?
Dialogue: 9,0:14:23.07,0:14:25.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was neither particularly big nor small.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:25.84,0:14:26.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about the shape?
Dialogue: 9,0:14:26.92,0:14:28.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't remember very well.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:28.76,0:14:29.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about color?
Dialogue: 9,0:14:29.50,0:14:31.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know. It was just a shadow.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:31.40,0:14:32.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A shadow...
Dialogue: 9,0:14:32.85,0:14:36.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, it looked like a human shadow against the light.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:36.32,0:14:37.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think so.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:37.75,0:14:39.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Against the light...
Dialogue: 9,0:14:39.19,0:14:42.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was night, so the only light source would have been the moon.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:42.44,0:14:44.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think so too.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:44.23,0:14:47.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The moon was quite bright last night.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:47.13,0:14:47.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that related—
Dialogue: 9,0:14:49.03,0:14:52.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda, when did you stop telling stories and go to bed?
Dialogue: 9,0:14:52.54,0:14:53.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ten o'clock.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:53.84,0:14:55.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How were the shutters at the time?
Dialogue: 9,0:14:55.12,0:14:57.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think they were closed.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:57.79,0:15:01.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the shutters were closed, there couldn't have been a shadow.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:01.71,0:15:03.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is becoming a hassle...
Dialogue: 9,0:15:04.11,0:15:07.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably best to go to the main building and take a look at room seven.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:07.17,0:15:09.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How wonderful! So mysterious!
Dialogue: 9,0:15:09.51,0:15:11.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad we took this trip!
Dialogue: 9,0:15:11.67,0:15:13.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish we hadn't.
Dialogue: 1,0:15:13.30,0:15:14.30,Sheet,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1.5\fn5\fs150\fnCorbel\b1\c&H000000&\frx350\fry0\pos(636.886,344.543)\frz0.1232}No Entry{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.30,0:15:14.30,Episode Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\p1\c&H167C8A&\fscx99\fscy94\pos(383.143,184.286)}m 263 187 l 1025 187 1000 363 286 363
Dialogue: 9,0:15:17.43,0:15:18.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 9,0:15:18.27,0:15:19.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, what is it?
Dialogue: 9,0:15:20.77,0:15:21.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:21.82,0:15:23.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm bad with kids.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:23.50,0:15:24.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:24.69,0:15:27.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kayo-san, could you spare a moment?
Dialogue: 9,0:15:29.25,0:15:31.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'd like to see the main building.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:31.91,0:15:33.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The main building?
Dialogue: 9,0:15:33.39,0:15:34.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 9,0:15:34.41,0:15:38.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're looking into the hanged shadow.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:38.19,0:15:40.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could you show us to room seven?
Dialogue: 9,0:15:41.36,0:15:43.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but I can't right now.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:43.58,0:15:46.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Onee-chan will get mad at me.{HNNNNNNNNNNNNGGGGGG}
Dialogue: 9,0:15:47.16,0:15:48.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then at least tell us this.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:48.89,0:15:51.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that room still used for guests?
Dialogue: 9,0:15:52.42,0:15:57.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. Guests only use the bath and the dining hall in the main building.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:57.55,0:15:58.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it's an empty room.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:58.93,0:16:02.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The second floor is used for storage.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:02.44,0:16:04.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I go now?
Dialogue: 9,0:16:04.69,0:16:06.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:06.09,0:16:07.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were very helpf—
Dialogue: 9,0:16:07.94,0:16:10.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She doesn't like me.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:10.01,0:16:13.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. I'm sure she's just scared of big men.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:13.91,0:16:15.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So cute!
Dialogue: 9,0:16:17.12,0:16:19.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it a problem if we can't see room seven?
Dialogue: 9,0:16:19.78,0:16:22.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not so much a problem as it is a hassle.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:22.00,0:16:24.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't see the scene of the crime.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:24.29,0:16:25.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:25.38,0:16:27.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These bring back memories!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.21,0:16:27.46,Open,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fay-0.15\fax0.5\blur1\fs60\fnBurst My Bubble\b1\c&H222525&\frz359.5\pos(916.8,242.051)}Rie{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.01,0:16:31.13,Open,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fay-0.15\fax0.15\blur1\fs60\fnBurst My Bubble\b1\c&H252A46&\frz359.5\frx358\fry26\pos(1008.69,397.022)}Rie{\b0}
Dialogue: 9,0:16:32.64,0:16:34.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Morning radio exercises...
Dialogue: 9,0:16:34.46,0:16:36.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't gone to those in two years!
Dialogue: 9,0:16:37.57,0:16:39.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You went until second year of middle school?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.64,0:16:41.06,Sheet,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fnFansub Block\pos(646.286,219.46)\fscx92\fscy100\c&H9CCBC6&}AAAAA
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.64,0:16:41.06,Sheet,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fnCorbel\b1\frx358\fry358\fscx73\fscy100\pos(646.317,218.397)\c&H123935&} Seizansou Annex{\b0}
Dialogue: 9,0:16:39.47,0:16:41.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 9,0:16:42.87,0:16:44.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's take a look from the back.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:46.81,0:16:48.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did it rain last night?
Dialogue: 9,0:16:49.44,0:16:50.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It was a passing shower.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:51.44,0:16:58.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To see a shadow against the light, both the east and west windows had to be open.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:58.88,0:16:59.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 9,0:17:01.07,0:17:03.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's time for lunch.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:04.94,0:17:06.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for the meal.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:10.84,0:17:14.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be wonderful to have a sister.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:14.18,0:17:17.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Did you wish you had a sister?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:17.29,0:17:18.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kind of.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:18.37,0:17:20.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, did you figure anything out?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:20.20,0:17:20.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:20.64,0:17:22.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're still just starting to look into it.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:22.46,0:17:24.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though I do have a theory.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:24.27,0:17:25.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Let's hear it.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:28.02,0:17:29.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:29.15,0:17:30.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:30.92,0:17:33.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you guys leaving me out of the loop?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:33.03,0:17:36.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Out of the loop or in, where the heck do you go all day?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:36.60,0:17:37.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see you at all!
Dialogue: 9,0:17:37.41,0:17:39.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't get it, do you?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:39.53,0:17:41.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're supposed to use a hot spring multiple times a day.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:41.95,0:17:43.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that how it works?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:43.38,0:17:44.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ta-da!
Dialogue: 9,0:17:44.53,0:17:45.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:45.11,0:17:46.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't my yukata cute?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:46.58,0:17:47.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's wonderful!
Dialogue: 9,0:17:47.79,0:17:48.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You look great!
Dialogue: 9,0:17:49.24,0:17:52.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got my parents to buy it for me at the start of summer break!
Dialogue: 9,0:17:52.32,0:17:53.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You always said you wanted one.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:53.87,0:17:55.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The pattern is good.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:55.24,0:17:56.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what's bad?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:56.93,0:17:58.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The obi.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:58.76,0:17:59.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an imitation.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:59.97,0:18:01.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt it's radioactive.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:01.69,0:18:04.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said "imitation", not "mutation".
Dialogue: 9,0:18:04.74,0:18:07.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The butterfly is a separate part from the obi.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:07.88,0:18:10.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't rightfully call that a yukata.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:10.03,0:18:12.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More useless information.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:15.89,0:18:17.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 9,0:18:18.86,0:18:23.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I've been cursed by the hanged shadow too?
Dialogue: 9,0:18:29.07,0:18:30.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go to the hot spring again today.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:31.27,0:18:32.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 9,0:18:32.50,0:18:35.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A hanged shadow.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:35.09,0:18:39.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A product of Ibara and Chitanda's fevered minds.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:39.06,0:18:40.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Withered flowers.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:41.14,0:18:43.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But something is missing.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:48.39,0:18:49.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go back together.{She knows what's up.}
Dialogue: 9,0:18:51.54,0:18:52.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi?
Dialogue: 9,0:18:55.29,0:18:58.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Weren't you just at the dining hall?
Dialogue: 9,0:18:58.84,0:19:00.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When did you get here?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:00.16,0:19:04.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you see, if you slide down the slope behind Seizansou, you come out right behind here.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:04.87,0:19:08.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll slide down a mountain for a shortcut?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:08.49,0:19:10.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Typical Satoshi behavior.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:14.38,0:19:18.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't think of anything that would appease Chitanda.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:18.77,0:19:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Explaining the shadow is simple.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:20.91,0:19:24.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The question is, why?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:25.39,0:19:27.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Houtarou, did you get dizzy again?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:27.48,0:19:30.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, were there any events last night?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:30.94,0:19:32.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You got dizzy in the bath.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:32.56,0:19:34.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anything {\i1}else{\i0}?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:34.85,0:19:36.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We all told ghost stories together.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:36.59,0:19:38.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had more flowers than hands.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:38.49,0:19:40.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I meant anything official.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:40.87,0:19:42.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, there was the summer festival.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:42.99,0:19:45.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't you hear the drums?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:45.26,0:19:47.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Drums?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:47.24,0:19:48.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right!
Dialogue: 9,0:19:48.66,0:19:50.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The summer festival!
Dialogue: 9,0:19:50.38,0:19:51.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see now...
Dialogue: 9,0:19:51.90,0:19:54.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what about it?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:01.27,0:20:03.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That shadow you saw...
Dialogue: 9,0:20:03.19,0:20:07.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was probably just a yukata on a hanger.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:10.80,0:20:13.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would it be hung there?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:13.05,0:20:17.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And why would someone open the windows specifically so we could see it hanging?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:17.33,0:20:17.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:17.73,0:20:20.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't so you could see it.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:20.23,0:20:20.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 9,0:20:21.29,0:20:23.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was to dry it.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:23.07,0:20:24.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The yukata was wet.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:24.86,0:20:29.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The windows were open to let the wind in so it would dry faster.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:29.62,0:20:30.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:31.21,0:20:32.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because it rained.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:32.55,0:20:35.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I mean, why was it hanging in room seven?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:35.50,0:20:39.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So no one could see it being dried.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:39.31,0:20:40.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we saw it!
Dialogue: 9,0:20:40.87,0:20:41.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:41.63,0:20:43.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To hide it from the rest of the family.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:44.32,0:20:46.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:46.16,0:20:50.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The one who hung it up to dry was Kayo.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:50.11,0:20:53.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kayo was envious of Rie's yukata and wanted to try it on.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:53.94,0:20:56.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm sure Rie wouldn't lend it to her.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:56.01,0:20:58.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not? They're sisters...
Dialogue: 9,0:20:58.48,0:20:59.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you notice?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:59.94,0:21:03.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rie wrote her name on her cup, stamp card, and ball.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:03.45,0:21:06.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She makes sure everyone knows what's hers.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:06.91,0:21:10.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kayo probably couldn't ask Rie to lend her the yukata.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:10.63,0:21:12.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But then...
Dialogue: 9,0:21:12.66,0:21:14.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, Kayo wanted to wear it.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:14.69,0:21:18.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So she secretly took it and wore it to the summer festival last night.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:18.81,0:21:20.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She left around eight o'clock.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:20.88,0:21:22.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kayo-san went to the summer festival?
Dialogue: 9,0:21:22.92,0:21:24.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw her.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:24.15,0:21:27.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I noticed someone leaving the house last night.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:29.46,0:21:32.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't sound like Kayo was around for the ghost stories, right?
Dialogue: 9,0:21:32.28,0:21:34.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right, she wasn't there.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:34.98,0:21:38.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Around that time, Kayo ran into trouble at the festival.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:38.98,0:21:40.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It started raining.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:41.66,0:21:44.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't last long, but the yukata was soaked.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:45.01,0:21:47.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kayo remembered that they were going to play with fireworks the next day.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:48.26,0:21:52.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She knew that Rie was planning to wear that yukata then.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:52.24,0:21:55.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She had to find a way to dry the yukata in time before Rie found out.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:56.59,0:22:00.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The family uses the first floor of the main building, and the annex was out of the question.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:00.67,0:22:02.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She couldn't use the dryer that late at night, either.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:02.85,0:22:06.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so, when everyone was asleep,
Dialogue: 9,0:22:06.44,0:22:10.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she snuck into the most distant room in the main building and hung the yukata up to dry.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:10.05,0:22:12.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But bad luck befell her again.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:13.06,0:22:17.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With the windows open, the moonlight made it look like a hanged shadow.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:18.96,0:22:23.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And even worse, we began to look into it.
Dialogue: 1,0:22:19.65,0:22:20.27,Sheet,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1.5\fn5\fs150\fnCorbel\b1\c&H1D2963&\frx350\fry0\pos(636.886,344.543)\frz0.1232}No Entry{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.65,0:22:20.27,Episode Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\p1\c&H308C94&\fscx99\fscy94\pos(383.143,184.286)}m 263 187 l 1025 187 1000 363 286 363
Dialogue: 9,0:22:24.21,0:22:26.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure Kayo felt like she was being cornered.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:26.69,0:22:31.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll bet the shadow behind the door was Kayo, too.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:31.91,0:22:33.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kayo-san...
Dialogue: 9,0:22:33.79,0:22:36.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She returned the yukata early in the morning.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:36.96,0:22:42.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike Rie, she goes to morning exercises every day, so putting it back was easy.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:44.21,0:22:45.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 9,0:22:45.90,0:22:48.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We should probably keep this from Ibara.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:48.48,0:22:51.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's better not to spark any trouble in the family.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:53.13,0:22:54.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But then...
Dialogue: 9,0:22:55.85,0:22:59.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that would mean those two don't get along.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:01.14,0:23:05.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you can't lend a yukata to your own sister...
Dialogue: 9,0:23:12.38,0:23:14.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's pretty normal. Siblings—
Dialogue: 9,0:23:14.95,0:23:18.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I always wanted a sibling.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:18.44,0:23:22.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An older sister I could look up to, or a cute little brother.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:26.91,0:23:29.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The siblings Chitanda imagines...
Dialogue: 9,0:23:30.63,0:23:33.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,may just be withered flowers.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:35.71,0:23:37.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's hot...
Dialogue: 9,0:23:40.94,0:23:42.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 9,0:23:42.15,0:23:42.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:55.38,0:24:00.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, maybe not {\i1}just{\i0} withered flowers.
